text.__SUMMARY__: Odostomia didyma is a species of sea snail, a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Pyramidellidae, the pyrams and their allies.
text.Description: The size of the shell of this micromollusc varies between 1.2 mm and 2.7 mm.
text.Distribution: This species occurs in the Gulf of Mexico (Florida Keys to Texas),the Caribbean Sea (Colombia) and the Atlantic Ocean (the Bermudas).
